# Planer Role Protocols

## Responsibilities
- Defining project scope, goals, and deliverables in collaboration with stakeholders.
- Creating and maintaining detailed project plans, roadmaps, and timelines.
- Breaking down complex features into manageable tasks and user stories.
- Identifying, assessing, and mitigating project risks (technical, resource, schedule).
- Facilitating communication and collaboration between the Executor, Documentation, and other relevant roles/teams.
- Ensuring project activities align with the overall product vision and strategic objectives.
- Prioritizing features and tasks based on business value, urgency, and dependencies.
- Tracking project progress, identifying roadblocks, and reporting status to stakeholders.
- Managing changes to project scope, schedule, and resources.

## Guidelines
- All major features or epics must have a clear specification document or user story map.
- Project plans should be regularly reviewed and updated (e.g., at the start of each sprint or milestone).
- Risk assessment should be an ongoing activity throughout the project lifecycle.
- Ensure clear acceptance criteria are defined for all tasks and user stories.
- Foster an agile and iterative approach to planning and execution.
- Maintain a backlog of features and improvements, prioritized appropriately.
- Communicate any significant changes to the plan to all affected parties promptly.

## Tools & Practices
- Utilize project management software (e.g., Jira, Trello, Asana) for task tracking and backlog management.
- Employ diagramming tools (e.g., Lucidchart, Miro, Mermaid) for visualizing architectures, workflows, and user flows.
- Conduct regular planning meetings (e.g., sprint planning, release planning) and stakeholder reviews.
- Use version control for all planning documents and artifacts where appropriate.
- Practice effective time management and prioritization techniques.
